Notes: Keystone Park was developed in two parts.  Keystone East. Original portion of park bounded by Soo Line RR (now Canadian National RR), Lake, Keystone and NorthWestern Rwy (now UP).  Land acquired in 1915 from Thatcher family, Jensen designed the park in 1917.  The overall layout has some original design left according to our investigation.  Keystone Park West.  Added circa 1919, Jensen's plan dates to then, bounded by Keystone, Lake, Thatcher and the UP RR with the northwest quarter of the block always private and never part of the park.  It has good integrity. There was a drive past the depot that is now a parking lot - it used to curve and extend to Keystone
